kernel_variant.question:
Let $S$ be the smallest set of positive integers satisfying
(a) $3\in S$;
(b) whenever $n^{2}\in S$ we also have $n\in S$;
(c) whenever $n\in S$ we also have $(n+4)^{2}\in S$.
Determine exactly which positive integers are 
NOT contained in $S$.
